The paper deals with multi-agent planning in non-cooperative dynamic games, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and robotics (cs.RO). The use of game theory to model the interactions between agents suggests that the paper could also be classified under the game theory subcategory (cs.GT). The paper also mentions the use of sensors and actuators, which are common in control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper uses iterative dynamic programming to solve the problem, which is a common technique in machine learning (cs.LG).
